      {
        "content": "Social media platforms often collect and share vast amounts of personal data without transparent consent, infringing on individual privacy rights. Users may unknowingly expose sensitive information, which can be exploited for targeted advertising, surveillance, or identity theft. This pervasive data collection undermines trust and autonomy, as individuals lack control over their digital footprints. The potential for misuse by third parties or breaches further heightens privacy concerns. Protecting privacy requires robust reforms, including clearer consent protocols, stronger data protection laws, and empowering users with greater control over their information. Without such measures, social media continues to pose significant risks to personal privacy.",
        "additional_kwargs": {
          "refusal": null
